        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 12:44PM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
        <description>At 1243 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Milltown, or 11 miles west of Poplar Bluff, moving southeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fairdealing, Budapest, and Milltown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
